 This statement is corroborated by many passages in the Acts, such as xviii.15;
 xxiii.29; xxv.9; xxvi.28, 32; xxviii.31.
 Claudius Lysias writes to the governor of Judaea that Paul was accused
 by his fellow-citizens, not of crimes deserving punishment, but on some
